						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone set up near the temple of Kallēśvara.</hi></p>						

						<p>Dhruva—undated.</p>						

						<p>This damaged hero-stone refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Dōrapparasa</hi> (Dhruva) and states that when <hi rend="bold">Mārakka-arasa</hi> was governing <hi rend="bold">Banavāsi</hi> and Binaēti (Binaēti) Abbe was administering the town (probably Siḍēnūr itself), a hero (name not clear) died in a fight. Reference has been made to <hi rend="bold">Siḍiyanūr</hi> and probably to a fight with the Gaṅgas.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
